AIR6500 will provide a Joint Air Battle Management System capability for the Royal Australian Air Force. The system will provide multi-domain integration of air, electromagnetic, and missile defence battle management including deployable & fixed operations centres, communications, and both active & passive sensors. The AIR6500 Hardware Engineering Lead as a member in the System Engineering Integration Team (SEIT) has the responsibility for providing technical guidance and ensuring design integrity and consistency of the Hardware components across the program throughout the project lifecycle. Your primary responsibility is to oversee and lead the Hardware technical aspects of the project, ensuring that all design and development activities are completed to the highest standard and meet the required technical specifications.

Responsibilities

Working on the AIR6500 project the Hardware Engineering Lead will provide services including but not limited to:

·         Provide oversight to all IPTs for Hardware development across the program

·         Drive the AIR6500 Hardware solution and interfaces in the architectural model to the AIR6500 solution

·         Review and guidance of Hardware and non-functional related requirements, product trades, and the sell-off approach

·         Work with IPTs and System Architects to establish hardware requirements and sizing for AIR6500 elements

·         Work with the SEIT Lead to drive the development of key AIR6500 technical documents and artefacts such as solution description, trade studies, and definition of requirements

·         Capture and assess Hardware metrics (e.g., on-time releases, quality / defect, supplier impact)

·         Work with a broad set of stakeholders across the Lockheed Martin Business and design partners for the achievement of common goals

·         Provide oversight and validation of subcontractor analysis reports

·         Provide cross skilling and knowledge transfer to LMA engineers

·         Desire to 'roll up the sleeves' and execute activities in addition to providing review and mentoring roles.

·         Drive development of AIR6500 deployable elements and ruggedized solutions for packaging hardware components.

·         Author technical documentation and develop Technical Data packs as required

·         Develop Test Plans, Procedures and Test reports as required

·         Perform Trade Studies to evaluate possible technical substitutions as required

 

About you:

To be successful in this role you will also have:

·         Extensive experience with hardware environmental qualification testing methods and standards

·         Extensive experience in the development and derivation of environmental requirements for COTS equipment

·         Extensive experience in undertaking gap analysis and compliance assessments for equipment environmental test reports

·         Significant experience in physical designs that are certified to operate at higher classification levels

·         Significant experience in arrangement of hardware solutions that operate at multiple security classification levels

·         Experience in optimising designs for operator and manned spaces

·         Expert experience in communicating, co-ordinating, prioritising and monitoring work progress towards a stated goal

Desired

·         Experience in comparison of and applicability across test methods and approaches for Military Standard Environmental Specifications (UT and NATO)

·         Experience in the design of field deployable and mobile military systems

·         Experience in design and analysis for optimisation of rack-based equipment to address thermal, emission coupling etc.

·         Experience in integration and verification approaches for hardware systems.

·         Understanding of analysis approaches and mitigation techniques for Co-Site RF designs

·         Any knowledge of packaging for ruggedized deployable land-based systems

·         Expertise across the systems engineering lifecycle, including architectural definition and analysis methods; test and integration.

·         Model-based System engineering experience (Rhapsody experience)

·         Requirement decomposition (DOORSNG experience)

 

An awareness of:

·         Ground-based Sensors

·         Ground based Effectors

·         Infrastructure software technologies include virtualisation, multilevel security, cyber defence, network accreditation, information assurance, system management

·         Infrastructure hardware technologies including computing (servers, clients, storage) network, cross domain solutions.

·         Agile Engineering Methodology

·         Configuration Management principals

·         Proven ability to design and develop innovative solutions to complex technical problems, and to think creatively and outside the box

·         Ability to lead and mentor junior team members, and to provide guidance and coaching on technical matters

How we reward and support you:

When you join Lockheed Martin, you work on projects you won’t experience anywhere else.

We offer you a range of benefits built to suit you, no matter what stage of life you are in. 

·         Flexible work & Hybrid work options

·         A variety of leave options including Purchase Leave to support you and your family

·         Learning & Development platforms to encourage ongoing self-development

A global, market-leading SaaS company operating in the AI-powered legal technology space, is currently expanding their engineering presence in Australia.

This is a rare opportunity to join as a founding engineer in a newly established Sydney-based engineering team, helping shape the technical direction, delivery standards, and culture from day one — while building highly scalable, customer-facing products used by thousands globally.




Huge progression opportunity & higher earning potential, with world class health care benefits!

Flexible Remote working, with just 1-2 days in their CBD office required weekly!





The Role:

Reporting directly to the Director of Engineering, you’ll join a high-calibre engineering organisation and play a key role in building out their APAC engineering hub.

You’ll work primarily with Ruby on Rails, contributing to large-scale SaaS platforms that combine AI-driven capabilities, elegant UX, and highly scalable backend systems.

No Rails? No problem! But you must be okay with learning it on the job. Other tech in their environment consists of TypeScript, React, Hotwire, Python, AI Tools & AWS Cloud Services.




Responsibilities:

Designing, building, and scaling high-performance web applications using Ruby on Rails & fullstack tech

Solving complex product and platform challenges with clean, maintainable solutions

Working across full-stack environments on a large-scale SaaS platform

Collaborating with distributed global engineering teams

Participating in architecture discussions and system design




Requirements:

Strong experience in Ruby on Rails development, alternatively with TypeScript, Python, JavaScript or C#

Working across full-stack technologies, ideally within a SaaS environment

Solid skills utilising AI tools and experience with working on AI centric projects is essential

Experience working across monolith and/or microservices architectures

Ability to thrive in fast-moving, collaborative product environments

About the program:

LMA has entered into an arrangement with BAE, Saab and CoA (MIWS) for the execution of all Combat System Integration work related to the Aegis Surface Combatant fleet. 

The agreement, called the Combat Systems Integration – Integrated Project Team (CSI-IPT) Collaboration Agreement or CCA forms a collaborative enterprise organisation to execute scopes of work across Hobart Class Destroyer (SEA4000 Phase 6 and other related Destroyer Capability Enhancement (DCE) upgrades) and the Hunter Class Frigates (HCFs - SEA5000 Phase 1). The CSI-IPT evolves the current independently executing programs such as SEA4000 Phase  6 and SEA5000 Phase 1 under an umbrella enterprise organisation formed as a program of programs. 

 

About the role:

We are seeking an experienced Technical Data Management professional to join our CSI-IPT DDG team, supporting a major Defence program.

This is an emerging leader opportunity suited to someone with experience in Data Management within Defence who is ready to step up and take ownership of program-level data activities. You don’t need to have held a formal Lead title before, we’re looking for someone confident in the work and ready to guide others.

In this role, you will ensure project documentation and technical data are delivered, controlled and compliant with contractual and Defence requirements. You will work closely with engineering teams, subcontractors and the customer to keep data flowing accurately and on schedule. 

Key responsibilities include:

Manage Data Management activities across the program

Manage customer data deliverables (CDRLs) and track comment resolution

Manage incoming subcontractor documentation (SDRLs) and support review processes

Ensure documentation meets contractual and company standards

Maintain technical records in accordance with Configuration & Data Management Plans

Support export-controlled and sensitive data compliance requirements

Provide guidance and mentoring to team members

Contribute to continuous improvement of Data Management processes

 

About you:

You are organised, confident and comfortable working with structured processes in a Defence environment. You understand how technical documentation and engineering data move through a program and enjoy working across multiple teams. 

Essential skills:

Experience in Data Management within Defence or complex engineering programs

Experience managing document deliverables such as CDRLs and SDRLs

Experience using CM/PLM tools such as Windchill or similar systems

Strong organisational and stakeholder engagement skills

Ability to manage multiple deliverables and priorities

An active Baseline security clearance (with eligibility to obtain NV1) and ability to handle Export Controlled information




Why join us:

Work on a complex, high-profile Defence program

Broaden your Data Management experience across engineering teams

Be part of a collaborative and supportive team environment

This is not a standard support engineering role.
  
You’ll be working on complex, custom-built mechatronic and motion systems deployed globally in high-profile, technically demanding environments. These are precision machines combining mechanical engineering, automation, controls and motion technology. When something needs diagnosing, validating or improving, you’re the person stepping in.
  
The role sits within a high-performing Service and Support team and blends mechanical depth with applied PLC and motion troubleshooting. It is hands-on, analytical and collaborative.
  
The Role
You’ll sit within a high-performing Service & Support team, providing mechanical and controls engineering expertise across new and existing installations.
  
Day to day, you will:

• Design and modify mechanical and mechatronic components
• Maintain SolidWorks models and technical drawings
• Perform core engineering calculations and validation
• Troubleshoot PLC systems including Beckhoff and Allen Bradley
• Diagnose servo, hydraulic and electric motion issues
• Conduct root cause analysis on complex faults
• Produce clear technical documentation and service notes
• Support global clients remotely and attend site when required
• Collaborate closely with engineers, designers and technicians
  
What You’ll Bring

• Degree in Mechatronics, Mechanical Engineering or similar
• Strong mechanical fundamentals with hands-on troubleshooting experience
• SolidWorks capability
• PLC exposure ideally Beckhoff and/or Allen Bradley
• Exposure to custom machinery or safety-critical systems is advantageous
• Australian Citizen or PR

Job Title: Engineering Manager - AI & Intelligent Automation - AWS
Ad Text:
Engineering Manager – AI & Intelligent Automation

Join a globally recognised intelligent automation and AI engineering team committed to building the next generation of AI‑infused automation solutions. This hands‑on leadership role blends engineering excellence, cloud architecture, AI agent development, and team uplift to deliver high‑impact outcomes across a large‑scale enterprise environment.

You will lead technical delivery across AI, ML, LLM orchestration, RPA, IDP, workflow automation, cloud engineering and intelligent automation platforms. Working closely with product, data and operations teams, you will shape automation strategy, uplift engineering maturity, and drive innovation across Westpac’s enterprise automation ecosystem.

What You’ll Do:
Provide hands‑on technical leadership across AI, machine learning, cloud engineering, robotics, IDP, workflow automation and intelligent automation technologies. 
Run experiments, build proofs‑of‑concept, and guide engineers through solution design, development and deployment.
Mentor and inspire a diverse team of automation specialists, fostering a culture of innovation, quality and continuous learning. 
Collaborate across product, engineering, data, security and operations to deliver aligned, high‑value outcomes.
Translate complex AI and automation concepts into clear, actionable insights for technical and non‑technical stakeholders. 
Drive and embed engineering best practices including Agile, CI/CD, automated testing, monitoring, observability and DevOps.

Stay ahead of emerging AI technologies (LLMs, BedRock, LangChain, AutoGen, agent frameworks, A2A patterns) and apply them to real‑world business challenges.
You will thrive in this role if you bring:

A strong track record delivering intelligent automation solutions in financial services or large enterprise environments. 
At least 3 years in engineering leadership and 5+ years delivering automation/AI/ML solutions.
Hands‑on cloud engineering capability across AWS and Microsoft Azure, with experience in ML/AI frameworks (BedRock, LangChain, AutoGen, Strands or similar). 
Ability to switch between individual contributor mode and orchestration/leadership mode.
Excellent stakeholder management, communication and influencing skills.
Experience working under pressure, delivering to tight deadlines and balancing multiple priorities.
Relevant certifications in cloud engineering (AWS/Azure) or intelligent automation platforms. 
Why Join Us?
Be part of a globally recognised automation and AI capability.
Build cutting‑edge AI agent and intelligent automation solutions.
Lead high‑impact engineering work in a major enterprise environment.
Work with modern AI/ML, automation and cloud technologies.
A culture of innovation, experimentation and continuous learning.

About Toshiba

Established in Australia in 1978, Toshiba International Corporation Pty Ltd (TIC) is a wholly owned subsidiary of Toshiba Corporation, Japan. TIC has established itself as a market leader in the power generation sector in Australia, providing industrial equipment, generators, turbines, transformers, motors, battery energy storage equipment and associated power infrastructure for this industry, including both the supply and installation of new equipment and the maintenance or upgrading of existing equipment. Our Company consists of engineering, technical, commercial and business development staff, with all staff focusing on customer needs (mostly the owners/operators and developers of power stations including thermal, hydro-electric, wind and battery energy storage and transmission and distribution plant).

Job Summary

With the recent growth in Digital Asset Management capability and workload, TIC is seeking a highly motivated Asset Management and Analytics Professional to join the ESS business.  The role is focused on working with our customers during the implementation and operation of our Asset Performance and Condition Monitoring Platform (Digital Twin), based on the EtaPRO® platform (https://etapro.com/).  As such, the role requires a working knowledge of power generation facilities, including steam turbine generator-based systems.  It is anticipated that the ideal candidate will bring process mechanical capability, broad thermodynamic knowledge and experience to this role.

Key Responsibilities:

Apply mechanical / process engineering knowledge across the ESS Asset Performance and Condition Monitoring business operations, including:

Working with the existing team to support the safe implementation and operation of online Digital Twin platforms for Toshiba Power Generation customers in Australia, New Zealand, Southeast Asia and other global regions

Providing engineering support to operations and maintenance activities / sustaining capital projects identified through the operation of the EtaPRO platform

Providing process / mechanical technical support to broader ESS business activities from time to time (for example capital project development activity associated with the deployment of Toshiba energy systems)

Work closely with Toshiba teams globally to understand Toshiba ESS Asset Performance and Condition Monitoring technology in order to effectively develop and deploy the technology across TIC regions of responsibility

Our ideal candidate will possess:

Relevant work experience in the power generation sector, including experience in steam turbine generator or boiler-based systems

Tertiary qualifications in Process, Mechanical or a relevant and related field of Engineering

Technical understanding of power generation facilities, including working at power station sites in operations, reliability or process engineering roles

Technical understanding of thermodynamic modelling

Project management experience (preferable)

Ability to work on-site and away from home when required

An Australian Driver’s License (essential)

 If you are looking for a role where you can genuinely add value and grow your career, we encourage you to apply via Seek.
